<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Newbridge Communications Inc., a special
interest book club, said it agreed to acquire closely held
Reader's Garden Inc., which operates two book clubs, for an
undisclosed price.
   Reader's Garden operates The Reader's Subscription for
readers of serious fiction, nonfiction and poetry, and The
Garden Book Club for serious gardeners.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Newbridge was previously known as Macmillan Book Clubs
until it was acquired by K-III Holdings L.P., an affiliate of
leveraged buy-out specialists Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co.,
in mid-1989. Newbridge had sales in excess of $100 million in
1989.
